subsection.p:
In order to evaluate the long-term level of Warfarin in the patient's system, we will want to fully understand the sum in this expression. This sum has the form
a+ar+ar^2+ \cdots + ar^{n-1}
where a=5 \times 0.08 and r=0.08. Such a sum is called a geometric sum geometric sum with ratio r. We will analyze this sum in more detail in the next activity.

li.p:
The nth partial sum S_n of the geometric series is

  S_n = a+ar+ar^2+ \cdots + ar^{n-1}
.
